HEADWORD: Jellyfish
<hw>Jel"ly*fish`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Any one of the acalephs, esp. one of the larger species, having a
jellylike appearance. See <er>Medusa</er> and
<er>acaleph</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

